## Problem 2 — All Subsets of a String

**Question:** given `"abc"`, return all possible subsets including empty.

```
output: ["", "a", "ab", "abc", "ac", "b", "bc", "c"]
```

**How to think about it:**

For each character you have exactly two choices — include it or skip it.

```
           ""
          /    \
        "a"    ""
       /   \  /  \
    "ab"  "a" "b" ""
    ...
```

```java
public List<String> subsets(String s) {
    List<String> result = new ArrayList<>();
    backtrack(s, 0, new StringBuilder(), result);
    return result;
}

private void backtrack(String s, int start,
                       StringBuilder current, List<String> result) {

    // BASE CASE — record current subset at every node, not just leaves
    result.add(current.toString());

    // EXPLORE — try adding each remaining character
    for (int i = start; i < s.length(); i++) {

        // 1. MAKE the choice — include s[i]
        current.append(s.charAt(i));

        // 2. RECURSE — move to next position
        backtrack(s, i + 1, current, result);

        // 3. UNDO — exclude s[i]
        current.deleteCharAt(current.length() - 1);
    }
}
```

**Key difference from permutations:** the `start` parameter. It ensures you only look forward — this prevents `"ab"` and `"ba"` from both appearing (they are the same subset).

**Trace on `"abc"`:**
```
call(start=0, current="")   → add ""
  include 'a' → current="a"
  call(start=1, current="a") → add "a"
    include 'b' → current="ab"
    call(start=2, current="ab") → add "ab"
      include 'c' → current="abc"
      call(start=3, current="abc") → add "abc", loop ends
      undo → current="ab"
    undo → current="a"
    include 'c' → current="ac"
    call(start=3, current="ac") → add "ac", loop ends
    undo → current="a"
  undo → current=""
  include 'b' → current="b"
  call(start=2, current="b") → add "b"
    include 'c' → current="bc"
    call(start=3, current="bc") → add "bc", loop ends
    undo → current="b"
  undo → current=""
  include 'c' → current="c"
  call(start=3, current="c") → add "c", loop ends
  undo → current=""

result = ["", "a", "ab", "abc", "ac", "b", "bc", "c"] ✅
```

